14 TO RECOGNIZE FEBRUARY 7-14, 2025, AS
15 NATIONAL MARRIAGE WEEK.
16
17 WHEREAS, marriage is the foundational relationship for all of society,
18 and good marriages are the bedrock of strong societies, for they are also the
19 foundation of strong families; and
20
21 WHEREAS, based on a wealth of academic research, married people tend to
22 have healthier lifestyles, longer life expectancies, more satisfying sexual
23 relationships, and more wealth and economic assets; and
24
25 WHEREAS, based on a wealth of academic research, healthy marriages
26 decrease crime, domestic violence, substance abuse, poverty, juvenile
27 delinquency, and suicide risk; and
28
29 WHEREAS, the effects of a healthy marriage on children are extremely
30 pronounced, since children who grow up with both a mother and father who are
31 married are much more likely to graduate from high school, obtain a college
32 degree, have higher earnings in adulthood, and do better academically and
33 emotionally; and
34
35 WHEREAS, healthy marriages save taxpayers throughout the nation
36 hundreds of millions of dollars annually by reducing many households' need
